    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cva-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model demonstrates sufficient evidence across assessed factors to support regulatory submission for the VAD indication. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation provides quantitative bounds on NIH predictions. Remaining factor gaps are acknowledged as areas for future model improvement but do not preclude the current submission given the conservative safety margins applied to the hemolysis acceptance threshold.",
